
Required packages:

python 2.7
pandas
numpy

To install, can use pip install


run the program by 'sh run.sh'

the grass raster maps are saved in ./grass/model and ./Data
the final speed map is saved in ./Data
the travel cost maps are saved in ./Data/costmaps

Input vector maps: emp_centers5, pop_center, chicago_road2
Input raster map:  landuse.gtif
Input speed chart: LU2Travel_Speed_Pan/nlcd_1992+lu2travel_speed.txt
python grasssetup.py     
		#transform emp_centers5, pop_center, landuse, and chicago_road2 to ascii files
		#inside ./Data directory
python centermap2indexlist.py
                #read center ascii to 100 centers and print list of (x, y, val) to 
                #popcenterlist.txt and empcenterlist.txt in ./Data directory
python landcover2speedmap.py 
		#generate speedmap using landuse, chicago_road2 ascii files and speedchart
		#to ./Data directory
                #Note that this map contains no actual speed, but square root of speed to be speed weight in deciding
                #random walk direction
python stocasticgreedy_randomwalk.py <vallessthan100> 
		#read either pop centers or emp centers from ./Data/popcenterlist.txt or ./Data/empcenterlist.txt
                #generate 800 files for each center
		#call this file 100 times
python reducemaps.py
		#convert the 100 travelcost maps to attractive maps. Replace all 0.0 with 0.001.
		#overlap the 100 maps using the weight of each attractive map
		#check infinite values: not done...

